Add Advanpix Mahler-measure early-exit API to MPSolve.

Introduces three thread-local entry points used by PSMM to abort MPSolve
root-finding as soon as one root's magnitude provably exceeds a given
threshold T (so M(p) > T regardless of remaining roots):

    void mps_mahler_set_threshold(double threshold);
    int  mps_mahler_is_over_threshold(void);
    void mps_mahler_mpsolve(mps_context * s);

Implementation mirrors mps_standard_mpsolve but consults a local stop
predicate (mps_mahler_check_stop) that trips `glb_over_threshold` on the
first root whose inclusion disk lies entirely outside |z| = T. Threshold
and flag are stored in TLS so the API is re-entrant across threads.

Authored against MPSolve 3.2.1; applies unchanged to 3.2.2.

Author: Pavel Holoborodko <pavel@advanpix.com>

